Bright Light Solar VCC Ltd is a registered S12J Venture Capital Company (FSB license no 47804) in terms of the Income Tax Act (SARS VCC reference number VCC-0060). S12J of the Income Tax Act allows investors to deduct the full cost of their investment against their taxable income, thereby obtaining a full tax write-off for their investment capital. As long as the investment is held for a period of 5 years or longer, there is no recoupment of this tax deduction. Benefits of the Bright Light Solar VCC structure to Investors: The tax deduction of capital invested; A fully managed process with no involvement required from the Investor; Semi-Annual dividend paid from year 1; Ongoing dividend for 25 years; Targeted year 1 dividend of 8.4%, growing annually; Targeted IRR of 17.5% after tax return; and The ability to trade investment after 5 years. Any individual, corporate entity or Trust, as a registered taxpayer in South Africa, automatically qualifies to invest in an approved S12J Venture Capital Company.

 At Aurinko Power, we understand to deliver winning solutions and profit to our clients and have developed project opportunities and led acquisition activities totalling 2,500 MW, and closed transactions of 347 MW PV capacity globally. We have an excellent understanding of the Australian and global market and industry, and have consulted with international organizations, such as UNDP-GEF, Government of Malaysia, US State Department, EC-ASEAN Energy Facility and World Bank. 
 
 We assist our clients in greenfield developments (feasibility and permitting stage), M&A activities (due diligence, cost modelling), business case and strategy development for new entrants to the Australian market, advice in supply chain and design activities, and manage implementation and transactions of larger-scale solar projects. 
 
 The outlook for our market is certainly very promising and Renewable Energy has very strong long-term drivers, however we will need to continue navigating the short-term uncertainties and challenges. Aurinko Power is here to help you with our target- and solution-focused approach.

Pacific Solar was created following 20+ years in the commercial electrical contracting industry based in Melbourne.
 We made the decision to diversify into grid connected solar power systems as an add-on to our existing electrical business....Today, solar is our primary direction.
 We’ve seen first-hand the power of solar, and how it helps business owners like you reduce energy consumption costs. And we’re determined to help other businesses see the light.
 
 We pride ourselves on delivering the highest quality installations at competitive prices while maintaining customer service and satisfaction as a priority.
 
 Over the years, we’ve empowered businesses big and small. Our goal is to lead the charge for commercial solar across Australia, and help businesses keep money in their own pockets, all while helping the environment.
 
 We believe that:
 * Businesses like yours should have the power to to generate, store, and use their own energy
 * Commercial solar is the key to a lower power bill and permanent savings
 
 Over the last 10 years, we’ve been doing just that. Businesses all over Australia trust Pacific Solar to deliver lower bills, positive ROI, and energy independence.

We specialise in High Quality Solar Systems: with or without Batteries, On or Off Grid, for home, work, Caravan, RV or Boat. We make it easy for you to go Solar no matter what your requirements might be.

Terrain Solar is an Australian owned and operated business that is developing innovative and strategically located solar farms across regional Australia. From initially locating suitable land and partnering with landowners, we take projects through engineering design, planning approval, grid connection, financing & investment stages and into construction and operation.

We are a solar electrical company that specialises in the service, maintenance and management of commercial solar systems, Australia wide.
 
 Experience has proven that proper maintenance of a solar system is essential to maximise both electrical production and the systems life. It supports and protects your warranties, maximises your financial investment and gives you peace of mind about electrical safety.
 
 Currently we look after over 100 large commercial solar sites offering a range of services from scheduled cleaning to total system management. 
 
 Services offered include solar panel cleaning, electrical inspection, reporting, rectification, installation, certification, remote monitoring up to full solar system asset management. 
 
 Finally, and most importantly all works are completed to the highest level by our inhouse team of trade qualified electricians.

We are a renewable energy fund with focus on commercial solar growth. Our model is funding, building and maintaining commercial solar systems throughout Australia and delivering value back to end energy users and building owners.
 
 Solar Bay was founded in 2017 by three budding energy enthusiasts to tackle the problem of renewable energy financing. Today Solar Bay owns and manages some of the largest rooftop solar systems in Australia. We work with installers, landlords, tenants and owner occupier
 Solar Bay is helping transition Australia away from fossil fuel based power plants in favour of distributed renewable generation. This means installing solar on every business that has the roof space or spare land available to capture the energy from the sun. Solar Bay prefers to own the solar infrastructure we install so we always know the systems are performing to their maximum, and weâ€™re providing the best available energy solutions to our clients.

Kuga Electrical is dedicated to providing businesses with their total energy needs, including solar electricity, LED lighting, solar battery storage, power factor correction and voltage optimisation. 
 
 With energy prices steadily rising and increasing operating costs, staying competitive is getting harder for businesses around Australia. Kuga Electrical want local businesses to have greater control of their energy by offering alternative energy solutions that can save money and help them become more efficient. Last year in Victoria alone, Kuga Electrical helped businesses save 34MW of electricity, resulting in $10 million in electricity cost savings.
 
 With its success in the Victorian market, Kuga Electrical has expanded to New South Wales and Western Australia, and there are plans for further expansion to South Australia and Queensland. 
 
 CEO John Kurta has over 15 years experience in the energy industry working across the sales and marketing functions. John started Kuga Electrical in 2017, and now manages around 70 staff of designers, consultants and technicians in the top 3% fastest growing companies in Australia. Kuga Electrical is always on the look out for highly motivated, customer-focused problem solvers who can help drive our business forward to even greater heights. 
 
 Kuga Electrical’s success can be attributed to a highly experienced team of professionals who always put the customer first. Just like a Cougar, the business strives to be fierce and agile in an effort to exceed customers’ expectations and develop stronger links with all our business partners and community.
